# What role should NATO allies play in providing military assistance to Ukraine?

## Summary
NATO allies have expressed their support for Germany's move to send 14 Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine and are advocating for the provision of more sophisticated weaponry, such as longer-range missiles, to Kyiv <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>. The United Kingdom, Poland, Finland and the Baltic states have been leading the charge for heavier military equipment, as both Ukraine and Russia are gearing up for new offensives <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>. Germany has called on the United States to send its own tanks to Ukraine, and a preliminary agreement has been struck for the U.S. to send M1 Abrams tanks <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. However, the Pentagon has expressed reluctance to involve itself in the logistical costs of maintaining the tanks <font color=#FF3399>[4]</font>. Ultimately, NATO allies should work together to provide Ukraine with two battalions, or 88 tanks, to strengthen their defensive firepower and help them secure a lasting peace <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>.

